f\nthe disk. At $10^{-4}\\,Z_\\odot \\leq Z \\lesssim 10^{-2}\\,Z_\\odot$, HI\nphotoionization heating acts as a dominant gas heating process and drives\nphotoevaporative flows with roughly a constant rate. The typical disk lifetime\nis shorter at $Z=0.3~Z_\\odot$ than at $Z = Z_\\odot$, being consistent with\nrecent observations of the extreme outer galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Jun 2017 16:22:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Mar 2018 08:40:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-02"}
