 is not a branching locus for the fundamental matrix solutions. The\nimportance of these results for the analytic theory of Frobenius Manifolds is\nexplained. An application to Painlev\\'e equations is discussed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jun 2017 10:28:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-18"}
